Un Gadget bizarre et anime: La Chose (507)
La navette Pifouz I et son lanceur (533)

description:
The Convict Commandos are not known to do things the conventional way. Titch Mooney, Jelly Jakes, Smiler Dawson and Guy Tenby - not forgetting their ruthless confederate Dr Jane Mallory - always get the jobs where conventional is not an option.

Even by their standards, though, a boat chase through the centre of Venice was a bit extreme.

You really have got to read this tale.
name: Convict Commandos: Brilliant Death

description:
Sergeant Jim Stark was trying to lead a lost patrol of fellow Chindits back to safety through a jungle swarming with Japanese. A tight enough spot for any man, even worse for Jim who had lost his memory.

But Jim didn't know the half of it.

Among the men of that lost patrol was a man already wanted in England for murder, a man whose burning dark eyes bored into Jim's back every time it was turned, a man who had to kill the sergeant or die himself!
name: Lost Patrol

description:
In the lead-up to the hastily organised evacuation at Dunkirk, a disparate group of servicemen found themselves thrown together.

A Pay Corps clerk...

an RAF policeman...

and a Royal Navy Able Seaman...

were joined by a shady civilian who was unsure whose side he was on, except his own.

They would have to combine their skills, intelligence and abilities if they were to live to fight another day.
name: A Motley Crew

description:
THE MEN - Tough British sailors schooled in the traditions of Trafalgar. Lean, hard-fighting Americans spurred on by the memory of Pearl Harbour.

THE SHIPS - MTBs of the Royal Navy - four torpedo tubes, six guns, capable of 40 knots. Patrol Torpedo Boats of the US Navy - four tubes, five guns, a top speed of 45 knots.

THE OBJECTIVE - To close with the enemy... FAST!
name: Full Speed East

description: On a war-ravaged alien world, the Doctor and Emily fight to save Matthew from the Advocate, while avoiding planetwide civil war and a space-and-time misplaced Edwardian Torchwood, still hunting the Doctor since The Time Machination! Everything leads to this poing - but who will die?
name: Final Sacrifice Part 1: Extraordinary Travellers

volume.name: Doctor Who: The Tenth Doctor Archives

description: Long live the Queen! As the war between the Soul Free and the Terror builds, the Doctor discovers who's really pulling the strings behind the scenes! And as 'Mr. Finch' faces off against Emily, Alexander Hugh and the Edwardian Torchwood agents choose their own sides in the coming war...
name: Final Sacrifice Part 2: Whirled War Too

volume.name: Doctor Who: The Tenth Doctor Archives

description: War! What is it good for?! The Doctor discovers the truth about Kol'Ne Wah and finds Matthew, while Emily and Hugh try to stop the world from rebooting! But what is the Advocate's terrible plan - and why are the fifth-dimensional Tef'Aree involved?
name: Final Sacrifice Part 3: Reunion

volume.name: Doctor Who: The Tenth Doctor Archives

description: Tragic loss… Final issue! Final appearance of the Tenth Doctor! Sad farewells. A song ends. People die. What, you thought we'd end on a high note? It's called 'Final Sacrifice', guys! Multiple Eagle Award-nominated writer Tony Lee and Matthew Dow Smith close the book on the tenth Doctor...
name: Final Sacrifice Part 4: End-Game

volume.name: Doctor Who: The Tenth Doctor Archives

description:
'Ground Control': The TARDIS is grounded by a safety officer who accuses the Doctor of using it as a weapon.

'The Big, Blue Box': A human who remembers a 'big blue box' appearing at important times in his life learns his true origins when he finally encounters the Doctor himself.

'To Sleep, Perchance to Scream': The Doctor's anxieties and guilt manifest themselves during a surreal dream.

'Old Friend': The Doctor answers a summons from a one-time companion named Barnaby Edwards, now elderly and in a nursing home, who carries out the Doctor's orders and delivers a package to the Doctor. Only problem is the Doctor hasn't met this companion yet in his time stream.
name: Ground Control; The Big, Blue Box; To Sleep, Perchance To Scream

volume.name: Doctor Who: The Tenth Doctor Archives

description: Katherine's hope for her beloved brother's return to their estate in Hampshire is dashed when she receives the news of his death... He met a brave death at Battle of Waterloo. Then cruel reality hits devastated Katherine. Her uncle's family claims the estate, leaving Katherine no access to her fortune. The only person she can turn to for help is Lord Adam Calthorpe, her late brother's superior. Little does she know her brother asked Adam to look after Katherine if any ill fate were to befall him...
name: Vol. 1

description: Katherine is rescued from her plight by Lord Adam Calthorpe, her late brother's senior officer, and Adam's mother, Lady Calthorpe. Katherine finds herself increasingly attracted to Adam, who fights with all his might to protect her. But his idea of an ideal woman is a blue-eyed, blond beauty. In comparison, unworldly Katherine lacks the grace of a lady. No matter. Lady Calthorpe, who sees an exceptional beauty and talent in Katherine, takes the matter into her own hands to make Katherine's social debut a big success. And so the social season begins.
name: Vol. 2

description: Our 8th compilation for Comixology of Aces Weekly - the award-winning on-screen comic art magazine featuring some of the world's finest creators of comic art. Published by David Lloyd, the guy who brought you V For Vendetta.
name: Volume 08

description: Alaric Moebius and Basil Fox travel from the lava pits of New Guinea to the sun-scortched Middle East in pursuit of a lost pyramid at the insistance of their mysterious billionaire benefactor known only as "The Collector." What is it about this lost treasure that he finds so important? And will the duo survive the slings, arrows, hand grenades, and bowie knives of angry natives, short-tempered amazonians, and hellbent undead mercenaries to find it? The one-shot adventure "The Devil's Handshake" is brought to you by Ryan Schifrin and the legendary Larry Hama (G.I. Joe, Wolverine)!
name: The Devils Handshake

description:
Perdit Puer Part 2

Issue two finds our hero trapped in a basement thrown down a pit of LSD. James' past haunts his mind and we begin to understand who he has become and why the Angel has chosen him.
name: Perdit Puer Part 2

description: The kids arrive at the Professor's creepy house and learn about Plan B - it'll be dangerous, but may end the zombie nightmare. Gabi calls her dad to make sure the family's safe, but Johannes can't leave his daughter trapped in a creepy house! Joined by son Ted, their roadtrip takes a quick turn from adventure to terror.
What will be the effect of Monica’s desperate move? The fourth and final part of the dark story of the Slavic bane brings a rather unexpected ending!

Physically exhausted after an intense all-nighter, Batman squares off against Bane for one last showdown! But does the Dark Knight have anything left? Will Bane finally crush his nemesis once and for all? And where's the Arkham Knight been all this time? Find out in the finale of "Bane of Existence"!
name: Bane of Existence Part 5 of 5

description: Bad news for Mack, but the fighting doesn't stop.

Part two of KJ Mendenhalls series covers the legend of Vlad Tepes. Forget the Hollywood takes that are more about entertainment than history. This story is pieced together from bits and fragments of the mysterious history of The Dragon himself. Vlad Tepes is excitement from the first to the last page as this old but incredible legend gets reinvigorated.
name: Vlad Tepes

description:
Throughout history, the chosen few have joined the ranks of the "Borough of Churches". A Secret order tasked with an ongoing battle to destroy the forces of evil. Charlie Swanson is the latest recruit. Trouble is, she didn't ask to join and doesn't give a damn about the B.O.C or what it fights for... Yet!

Charlie "Chuckles" Swanson was a normal everyday NYC police officer, doing her bit to make the world a better and safer place. That was until a random encounter awakened a dormant gene causing a transformation into a human vampire hybrid.

Discover the secret order of the "Borough of Churches", directly from Charlie who will tell you her story the only way that she can... with humour, horror and a whole lot of blood!

Issue #2

During a late night police call out, Charlie is attacked by a rogue vampire and infected with the "feeder" gene. This sparks a series of events that quickly spiral out of control and leave Charlie's future and survival in jeopardy.

A mutated cybernetic boar searches for his place in the world. Looking for peace, Cy-boar usually finds only danger, and skull splitting action!

CY-BOAR #3: THE ENFORCER

Choosing to work for the enigmatic Mr. Q, Cy-Boar turns to a life of crime! Also, there is an old man in the robotic exo-suit who wants Cy-Boar's hide!
name: The Enforcer

description:
Know you enemies

After Hitoshi's crushing loss at the hands of an unknown group he embarks on his journey of vengeance.

But are things bigger they what they initially appear and what new hell awaits?
name: Know You Enemies

description:
Restaurants, Fast Food Joints and the Meals you Cook at Home

After finding out his microwaved cat food hot dish tastes awful because he does not have enough sugar- Bob finally decides to adventure outside and visit his favorite restaurant- Ed's Cafe. Meanwhile, Jeff is (once again..) stuck working on the 4th of July.

It's the following morning and Bri prepares to be on her way. However, an unexpected event leaves her stuck on P40 with no access to her resources. Another chance meeting with Dan results in a kind offer of help--as well as opening the door to a past that Bri would prefer to forget.
name: Part 2

description:
Faction 3 brings you a big, colourful poke to the eyeballs, with stories ranging from the gut-wrenching to the bizarre. Featuring some of New Zealand's premier comic artists, the third anthology in the series is a wild, rollicking ride, and an inspiring introduction to the New Zealand comic scene.

Contributing artists include Tim Gibson (Moth City), Li Chen (Extra-Ordinary), Jonathan King, Toby Morris, Mat Tait and Michael Brown, Katie O'Neill and Cory Mathis, with a cover by Ben Stenbeck (Baltimore).

Includes Tim Gibson's The Reservoir, in colour for the first time.
name: Vol. 3

description: Pam goes on a strange journey to a mountain monastery. Guest artist Tyrell Cannon (Victus) illustrates eight pages. Falling Rock National Park is a comic strip that takes place in a southwestern national park. Park Ranger Dee looks after animal residents Carver, Ernesto, Pam, and Melissa. Funny and sweet, Falling Rock is a pleasant place to visit.

Featuring 3 tales of the surreal, fantastic & macabre:

SÉANCE: At the height of spiritualism, a small group convenes to seek the aid of a medium in contacting their dearly departed.

REDEEM: Enigmatic saviors recover the body of an astronaut adrift in the void of space.

STINK EYE: A party of adventurers do battle with an unfamiliar monster that might be the group's undoing.
name: Book Four
